That is the location of the aftermarket radiators for the A/C systems on
buses. They worked pretty well, so I am sure a radiator would work there as
well. Probably two in series would be enough to cool a small motor. However,
it would be wise to put an aluminum metal expanded aluminum mesh over the
radiator(s) to keep large rocks from denting the vanes. That is what the AC
units used.

The A/C units also used two electric fans per radiator, so I am sure a
regular radiator would need a large cooling fan as well.

Jon Stiles
'68 Double Cab
'78 Westfalia

